$ SQL Server: buffer cache
@ buffer cache

The *buffer cache* is also referred to as *buffer pool*.

The purpose of the buffer cache is to reduce disk I/O and thus increase the performance of an → development/databases/SQL-Server/architecture/instance[SQL Server instance].
This is achieved by caching the content of → development/databases/SQL-Server/architecture/page[pages] in → development/databases/SQL-Server/architecture/memory-management[memory].

The content of the buffer cache is revealed in the → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/sys/objects/views/dm/os/buffer/descriptors[`sys.dm_os_buffer_descriptors` view].

sa:

  → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/sys/objects/views/allocation_units[`sys.allocation_units`]

  → development/databases/SQL-Server/architecture

  → development/databases/SQL-Server/architecture/checkpoint,
  → development/databases/SQL-Server/architecture/page

  Compare with → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance/SGA/database-buffer-cache[Oracle's buffer cache]
